Bank Asya to Refinance $250 Million Loan in April, Dunya Reports

-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 
2011-02-24T07:40:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-24/bank-asya-to-refinance-250-million-loan-in-april-dunya-reports.html
  Asya Katilim Bankasi AS , an
Istanbul-based Islamic bank, will refinance a $250 million
syndicated loan in April, Dunya reported, citing chief executive
Cemil Ozdemir.  The lender known as Bank Asya, plans to open 20 branches
this year to increase the total number to 200, Ozdemir said,
according to the Istanbul-based newspaper. Bank Asya provided a
120 million-euros, four-year loan to Dedeli Elektrik which is
building two gas-fired power stations with total 286-megawatts
capacity in Bilecik and Afyon in western  Turkey , Dunya quoted
Ozdemir as saying.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
